# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Jellyfin management server — where the real settings live
#
# There is NO top-level .env to fill in. All runtime configuration lives in:
#
#       server/.env
#
# docker-compose.yml loads it via `env_file: ./server/.env` for the backend.
# The admin (nginx) container needs no env file.
#
# To configure:
#       cp server/.env.example server/.env
#       # then edit server/.env  (or just run ./install-linux.sh, which does this)
#
# The settings you actually care about (full docs + defaults are in
# server/.env.example):
#
#   ADMIN_USERNAME           Login name for the web dashboard.
#   ADMIN_PASSWORD           Login password — CHANGE THIS before going live.
#   JWT_SECRET               Random secret that signs admin sessions.
#                            Generate one with:  openssl rand -hex 32
#   PORT                     Backend API port (default 4000). Leave it.
#   ONLINE_WINDOW_SECONDS    A unit is "online" if it heartbeated within this
#                            many seconds (default 90).
#   DB_PATH                  SQLite file location (default ./data/jellyfin.db,
#                            which is the mounted ./data volume in Docker).
#   ADMIN_ORIGIN             Allowed browser origin for direct API calls
#                            (dev only; the Docker setup is same-origin).
#
# This file exists only as a signpost. Copy it for your own notes if you like.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
